In the first shooting, a 13-year-old boy was gunned down in WesBank on Sunday. CAPE TOWN - Police has called on Cape residents to come forward with any information after two teenagers were shot dead in separate incidents.In the first shooting, a 13-year-old boy was gunned down in WesBank on Sunday.On the same day, a 16-year-old was shot dead in Kalksteenfontein.Hours later, a 33-year-old was killed and a youth wounded during a shooting in Manenberg.The police's Noloyiso Rwexana says: The circumstances surrounding these incidents are under investigation. A case of murder and attempted murder has been opened. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)